## Context

Skyes Over London is the primary product. Eclipse Theia is a dependency and upstream framework — not the owner, not the product name. All owned product-wrapper surfaces must reflect Skyes Over London. Upstream vendor source inside `vendor/theia/` and `vendor/theia-ide/` is intentionally untouched until a planned upstream rewrite pass, documented below.

---

## Scope Rules

- **In scope now:** Any file we author and control — CI workflows, package.json metadata, electron-builder configs, app HTML/JS, docs, changelogs, launcher/updater plugins, scripts.
- **Deferred (Theia upstream rewrite pass):** Files under `vendor/theia/` and `vendor/theia-ide/` that come from the Eclipse Theia project. These need a separate planned rewrite to avoid merge conflict debt.
- **Never touch:** Copyright notices inside upstream Eclipse Theia source (`NOTICE.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `SECURITY.md` in vendor/theia) — those are legal attribution requirements.

